Foreign-born blacks made up 3.1 per cent of the black population in 1980 . 
 That number has been on rise and they were 8.7 per cent of group in 2013 . 
 Majority of immigrants are from Jamaica, Haiti, Ethiopia and Nigeria . 
 Black immigrants more likely to have college degree and have a higher income and are less likely to live in poverty than the US-born population . 
 Foreign-born blacks are now large part of population in NYC, DC and Miami . 
 